 EDUCATION
 A Computer Science degree is preferred. An advanced degree is a plus. 
 
 
Provides direction, leadership, and specialist knowledge to Cloud Solution team in designing, demonstrating and deploying Oracle Cloud architectures that address customer business problems. Guides team to drive Oracle Cloud customer consumption through accelerating the adoption of Oracle cloud services.
 
 
Directs and manages resources, through managers, to work with customers, sales, engineering, and product teams to design and implement solutions for customers. Participates in the development and communicates business objectives and metrics to team. Sets objectives, implements plans, ensures attainment of business strategy. Manages the implementation of solutions and ensures successful deployments including code development and scripting. Oversees the support of customers from Proof of Concept (POC) through production deployment, resource configuration, planning, and customer education/training. May assist in developing solutions strategy on Oracle cloud solutions and technology to assist in gathering requirements, developing architectures and translating business needs into solutions. May assist in strategic direction on technical cloud solutions and customer success. May create and distribute technical assets (white papers, solution code, blog posts, and video demonstrations). Identifies gaps and enhancements to influence engineering roadmaps for customer driven features. May deliver presentation demonstrations to high level customers and at conferences and events. Maintains expertise by staying current on emerging technologies. Acts as spokesperson for Oracle cloud and an escalation path for relationships. Ensures team members maintain productive relationships for successful design and implementation of solutions. Builds trusted relationships with customers, sales, engineering, and other pillar counterparts. 
 
 
 Minimum qualifications include: 12 years experience with computer applications and tools required. Ability to travel 50% international and domestic.
 Preferred but not required qualifications include: Bachelor of Science-level university degree in Computer Science, Math, Engineering from accredited university; and/or relevant 12 years technical experience. Advanced degree in relevant field of studies highly desirable. 7 or more years of previous relevant technical management experience with computer applications and tools, including 2 or more of years as a second level manager. 2 or more years participation in the development of short, medium and long term plans to achieve strategic objectives in the field of computer applications and tools. 2 or more years of experience interacting across functional areas with senior management or executives to ensure unit objectives are met. Expertise in and an in depth and thorough knowledge of competitive and industry knowledge in the field of computer applications and tools; Influencing thinking or gaining acceptance of others; System and application design; Implementation of advanced product features; Project management; Solving technical problems with customers in technical environments; Written and verbal communication and interpersonal skills. 12 years experience and expertise in the clear communication of technical information to others through presentations, demonstrations, written communication and consultative solutioning experience. 
 
 
